#: ../../source/user_guide/elements_and_quadrature.rst:4
#: 9f3857fbead6434abcc4bc68db178922
msgid ""
"Every entry in :attr:`~tensormesh.Mesh.cells` is keyed by an *element "
"type string* — ``\"triangle\"``, ``\"hexahedron27\"``, ``\"wedge\"``, and"
" so on — that maps to one of the seven reference shapes in "
":mod:`tensormesh.element`. The element classes carry the basis-function "
"definitions and quadrature rules that the assembler uses internally; you "
"rarely call them directly, but understanding what they expose makes the "
"rest of the pipeline (assembly, IO, higher-order solves) less mysterious."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/elements_and_quadrature.rst:13
#: 1adc948e8a614493a03e628598720e62
msgid ""
"This page is laid out in two parts. First, the catalog of supported types"
" and the high-level rule for going from ``order=1`` to higher-order "
"solves. Second, a guided tour through the **reference → physical "
"pipeline** that turns a static reference-element definition into the per-"
"element shape values, gradients, and integration weights an assembler "
"actually consumes."
msgstr ""

