#: ../../source/user_guide/elements_and_quadrature.rst:475
#: aaa0933efaf940d4b4dd160d3021c0d5
msgid ""
"The reason the pipeline matters even when you only use "
":class:`~tensormesh.Transformation` is that **each attribute has a fixed "
"cost and a fixed memory footprint**, both controlled by exactly two "
"knobs: the element type (sets :math:`N_b`) and the quadrature order (sets"
" :math:`N_q`). When you write a custom assembler and reach for "
"``t.shape_grad``, you now know that what you are holding is a "
":math:`[N_e, N_q, N_b, D]` tensor built by composing "
"``get_basis_grad_fns`` (Step 3) with ``get_quadrature`` (Step 4) and the "
"per-element inverse Jacobian (Step 6)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/elements_and_quadrature.rst:485
